so for reading into notifications & gcm, dig into this and/or sandbox the code for how to set them on screen, <https://developer.android.com/training/notify-user/build-notification.html>
and then for expanded options, <https://developer.android.com/training/notify-user/expanded.html>
Read through the pendingIntents, we will launch into a NotificationsActivity

For gcm,
this SO has a nice minimum code for a service (plus the accepted answer)
<https://stackoverflow.com/questions/32237588/gcmlistenerservice-client-side-notification>
then for the docs, familiarize with this: 
<https://developers.google.com/android/reference/com/google/android/gms/gcm/GcmListenerService>

So that we aren’t blasting out gcm pings all the time, we will want to set up a mock service to start developing. So if while you’re digging into the workings of notifications & gcm pushes, think of a good way we could trigger the receiver (along the lines of putting it in with shake or something and firing an intent)

Then finally, we will need to create a database to store received notifications and that full-screen, in-app Notifications feed will be more just a standard Android activity that will display whatever is in that notifications db (it shouldnt worry about any of the gcm & notifications stuff) 

There’s a rough overview, we can have a dev meeting and break that down into tasks this afternoon
